snippet.textDisplay:
I love all the psudoscience with shocking nerves into ignoring you body's normal regular pains, and people thinking that means it's somehow fixing your problems when really you're just doing superficial damage to your body.

Putting your body to an extreme situation, like temperature shock, the sense of relief and endorphins released from the experience will make it seem like you're fine when actually your body is still just as bad, if not worse, than when you started.

He outed himself when he admitted that the sourness going away isn't permanent and you'll just feel it again later.
